+# ExecHealth Freeze ACL / sealed-state (v1)
+
+Purpose:
+- deny direct `HSET/HDEL/DEL/UNLINK/EVAL/EVALSHA` against freeze-control/state surfaces via Redis ACL
+- allow trusted services to mutate projections only through Redis Function entrypoints (`FCALL`)
+- monitor denied attempts with `ACL LOG`
+
+Keys:
+- `cfg:orderflow:exec_health:freeze_control:v1`
+- `metrics:exec_health:slo:autoguard:state`
+- `cfg:orderflow:exec_health:auto_freeze:v1`
+
+Bootstrap:
+- run `python orderflow_services/exec_health_freeze_acl_bootstrap_v1.py`
+- provision dedicated Redis ACL users for reader / writer / bootstrap roles
+- set `EXEC_HEALTH_FREEZE_SEAL_SECRET` on trusted writers
+
+Expected behavior:
+- direct manual hash edits are denied at Redis ACL layer and appear in `ACL LOG`
+- trusted writers update control/state only through sealed Redis Functions
+- if a hash is somehow modified outside entrypoints, seal verification fails and tamper-guard re-freezes
